            <h2>About Mr. Narendra Modi</h2>
            <p>
                Narendra Damodardas Modi, born on September 17, 1950, in Vadnagar, Gujarat, is an Indian politician who has made a significant mark in the country's political landscape. He is renowned for his role as the 14th Prime Minister of India, a position he has held since May 2014.
            </p>
            <p>
                Mr. Modi's journey in politics began as a member of the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS), a Hindu nationalist volunteer organization. He later joined the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP), where his dynamic leadership and vision propelled him to prominent positions.
            </p>
            <p>
                Before becoming Prime Minister, Mr. Modi served as the Chief Minister of Gujarat from 2001 to 2014. His tenure in Gujarat was marked by several developmental initiatives and economic reforms, earning him recognition for his governance skills.
            </p>
            <p>
                As Prime Minister, Mr. Modi has introduced and implemented various transformative policies and initiatives, such as "Make in India," "Swachh Bharat Abhiyan" (Clean India Campaign), and "Digital India," aimed at fostering economic growth, cleanliness, and digitalization across the nation.
            </p>
            <p>
                Mr. Modi's leadership style and commitment to improving the lives of the citizens of India have left an indelible mark on the nation's history.
            </p>
        </div>
